Title : Portal:Current events/2014 May 5
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|05|05}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]] and the [[Siege of Sloviansk]]
**A [[Ukrainian military]] helicopter patrolling around the [[Eastern Ukraine|eastern]] city of [[Sloviansk]] is shot down; all of the pilots survived and were later rescued.  [http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/05/world/europe/ukraine-crisis/index.html (CNN)]
**Neighbouring Ukraine and breakaway [[Transnistria]], [[Moldova]] places its borders on alert as the unrest continues. [http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/E/EU_MOLDOVA_UKRAINE?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&CTIME=2014-05-05-16-48-17 (AP)]

;Arts and culture
*Russian media reveals that President [[Vladimir Putin]] secretly [[Decree of the President of Russia|signed a decree]] (No. 279) honoring more than 300 journalists for their "objective coverage" of [[Crimea]]'s seizure from Ukraine. [https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/05/05/us-ukraine-crisis-media-idUSBREA440NJ20140505 (Reuters)]
*Russian actress [[Tatiana Samoilova]] dies at age 80. [http://www.themoscowtimes.com/news/article/soviet-film-star-tatiana-samoilova-dies-at-80/499414.html (''Moscow Times'')]

;Business and economy
*[[Target Corporation|Target]] announces that their chief executive and chairman, [[Gregg Steinhafel]], has resigned.  [https://www.bbc.com/news/business-27283872 (BBC)]
*[[Advanced Micro Devices]] expands a licensing agreement with [[ARM Holdings]] that may allow AMD to become a more aggressive competitor in the market for chips outside the PC realm. [https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/05/05/us-amd-chips-idUSBREA440OO20140505 (Reuters)] 

;Disasters and accidents
*[[2014 Po Toi Island ship collision|Eleven people are missing]] after a Chinese cargo ship collides with a [[Marshall Islands]] registered [[container ship]] off the coast of Hong Kong. [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/may/05/cargo-ships-collide-hong-kong-hong (The Guardian)]
*[[2014 Aegean Sea yacht and dinghy capsizing|At least two people are dead and 30 missing]] after two boats carrying illegal immigrants collide in the [[Aegean Sea]] off the coast of Greece. [http://www.680news.com/2014/05/05/greece-says-2-dead-30-missing-after-migrant-ships-sink-in-aegean-sea/ (AP via 680 News)]

;Health
*The [[World Health Organization]] states that the spread of [[polio]] is an international public health emergency. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-27284389 (BBC)][https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/06/health/world-health-organization-polio-health-emergency.html (New York Times)]
*[[The Coca-Cola Company|Coca-Cola]] and [[PepsiCo]] said they will remove [[brominated vegetable oil]] (BVO) from their drinks. [http://bigstory.ap.org/article/mtn-dew-latest-drop-controversial-ingredient (AP)]

;Law and crime
*The [[U.S. Supreme Court]] rules that a practice of beginning legislative sessions with prayers does not violate the [[Establishment Clause]] of the First Amendment. [http://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-nn-supreme-court-religion-catholics-jews-20140505,0,5918654.story (''Los Angeles Times'')]
*[[2014 Chibok kidnapping]]:
**[[Naomi Mutah Nyadar]], the leader of the [[One Million Women]] protest in [[Nigeria]] over failure to act on the kidnapping of 203 schoolgirls by terrorist group [[Boko Haram]], is reportedly detained on the orders of [[First Lady of Nigeria]] [[Patience Jonathan]]. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-27283278 (BBC)]

